    <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
    <div class="wrapper">

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Context</h1>
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Marketplace growth depended on providers maintaining active inventory</h3>

          </div>
        </div>


        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>BabyQuip is a two-sided marketplace where independent providers, called QPs, manage inventory, delivery, setup, pickup, and customer coordination.</h5>
            <h5>As the marketplace expanded into new gear categories, the business faced a supply problem:</h5>
            <h5 class="fontWeight200 greyBg200 paddingXS borderRadiusXS">
              👉 new categories existed, but providers rarely added inventory to them.
            </h5>
          </div>

        </div>
        <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">The original request</h3>

            <h5>The original request from leadership was to improve category discoverability by adding a new “discovery” tab inside the provider portal.</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="diagram_original_request.png" alt="original request: adding a new “discovery” tab inside the provider portal">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">The deeper issue</h3>

            <h5>After joining the project, I found the deeper issue was not category visibility itself, but the operational friction required to manage inventory.</h5>
            <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            <h5>Providers were not trying to manage storefronts as a primary activity. </h5>
            <h5>Most QPs were busy handling:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> delivery logistics</li>
              <li> cleaning and maintenance</li>
              <li> weekly scheduling</li>
              <li> customer coordination</li>

            </ul>
            <h5>Inventory management became secondary operational work with low perceived ROI.</h5>
            <h5>As inventory complexity increased, the effort required to maintain listings increased even faster.</h5>
            <h5 class="fontWeight200 greyBg200 paddingXS borderRadiusXS">
              👉 most QPs do not have time to update inventories
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>


  <section id="constraint" data-nav="constraint">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Constraint',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Constraint</h1>
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Marketplace expansion required more provider inventory.</h3>
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">But providers avoided inventory maintenance because the workflow was operationally expensive.</h3>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Core findings</h3>

            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> Editing inventory required 4–5 clicks with repeated navigation and context switching</li>
              <li> Inventory was fragmented across multiple views without a unified overview</li>
              <li> Filters reset during navigation, forcing providers to repeatedly re-orient themselves</li>
              <li> Unlisted and underused gear remained buried inside separate management flows</li>
              <li>New category expansion relied on providers actively maintaining inventory, but the workflow discouraged ongoing updates</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h6><span class="fontWeight400 grey900">Legacy Flow:</span> Fragmented, navigation-driven updates that reset provider context</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint1.png" alt="Inventory spread across multiple screens">
            <h6>Inventory spread across multiple screens</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint2.png" alt="4–5 clicks to edit a single item">
            <h6>4–5 clicks to edit a single item</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint3.png" alt="Changing categories requires restarting the flow">
            <h6>Changing categories requires restarting the flow</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint4.png" alt="Unlisted gear not surfaced in primary workflow">
            <h6>Unlisted gear not surfaced in primary workflow</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Internal marketplace data showed:</h3>
            <table>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th class="fontWeight400">QP segment</th>
                  <th class="fontWeight400"># of QPs</th>
                  <th class="fontWeight400">Supply index</th>
                  <th class="fontWeight400">Interpretation</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="colorBgYellowVW100">
                  <td class="fontWeight400">Top 10%</td>
                  <td>559</td>
                  <td>46.3%</td>
                  <td>High-volume QPs with the most complete listings</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="fontWeight400">Next 20%</td>
                  <td>1,117</td>
                  <td>31.7%</td>
                  <td>Mid-tier QPs with moderate listing depth</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="fontWeight400">Remaining 70%</td>
                  <td>3,913</td>
                  <td>21.9%</td>
                  <td>Smaller catalogs or lower platform engagement</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> the top 10% of QPs contributed 46.3% of total supply</li>
              <li> high-volume providers managed the largest and most complete inventories</li>
              <li> improving workflows for these providers created disproportionate marketplace impact</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="fontWeight200 greyBg200 paddingXS borderRadiusXS">
              💡 High-volume providers created disproportionate marketplace impact
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Inventory depth & marketplace supply</h3>
            <h5>In a two-sided rental marketplace, inventory depth directly impacts customer choice, search relevance, conversion opportunity, and category expansion. Improving provider maintenance workflows was therefore not only an operational UX problem, but also <span class="fontWeight400 grey900">a marketplace supply problem</span>.</h5>
            <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Reducing friction inside provider workflows became the highest-leverage path to improving long-term marketplace supply quality.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ inventory maintenance</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ marketplace depth</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ customer experience</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ business growth</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Insight</h1>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>The original proposal focused on adding another discovery surface.</h5>

            <h5>But discovery outside the operational workflow would likely fail because:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> providers already avoided inventory management due to time cost</li>
              <li> additional tabs created more navigation overhead</li>
              <li> discoverability separated from editing created another disconnected destination</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="spacingSmall"></div>

            <h5>The problem was not lack of visibility.</h5>
            <h5>The problem was:</h5>
            <h5 class="fontWeight200 greyBg200 paddingXS borderRadiusXS">
              👉 inventory management itself was too operationally expensive.
            </h5>
            <h5 class="fontWeight200 greyBg200 paddingXS borderRadiusXS">
              👉 Discovery is not a visibility problem. It’s an operational friction problem.
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>





  </section>


  <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

  <section id="reframe" data-nav="reframe">

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Reframe',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Reframe</h1>
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">The project shifted from discoverability to operational efficiency</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Original ask</h3>
            <h5>Add a dedicated tab to improve category discovery.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Reframed problem</h3>

            <h5>Discovery fails if inventory management itself is painful</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900"> Explored 2 strategic directions</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Option 1 — Separate discovery surface</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe_opt1.png" alt="Option 1 — Separate discovery surface">

            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Pro</h5>
            <ul>
              <li> increased visibility of new categories</li>
              <li> aligned with original stakeholder request</li>

            </ul>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Problems</h5>
            <ul>
              <li> required providers to leave inventory workflows</li>
              <li> introduced another destination to manage</li>
              <li> unlikely to become part of routine operational behavior</li>
              <li> preserved fragmented workflow structure</li>

            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Option 2 — Embedded discovery within inventory management</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe_opt2.png" alt="Option 2 — Embedded discovery within inventory management">

            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Pro</h5>
            <ul>
              <li> combined editing and discovery into one operational flow</li>
              <li> reduced interaction cost</li>
              <li> surfaced listed and unlisted inventory during existing tasks</li>
              <li> supported ongoing inventory maintenance without extra navigation</li>

            </ul>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">

            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">After internal reviews with product leadership and engineering, we aligned around Option 2.</h5>
            <h5>The challenge shifted from adding another destination to embedding discovery into existing operational behavior.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>The remaining design challenge became:</h5>
            <h5 class="fontWeight200 greyBg200 paddingXS borderRadiusXS">
              👉 how to embed discovery into inventory management without increasing cognitive overhead</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>



      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Core product principle</h3>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li>Discovery features outside the core operational workflow are rarely adopted.</li>
              <li>Embedding discovery directly into inventory management makes exposure part of routine usage instead of requiring intentional exploration.</li>

            </ul>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>



    </div>
    <div class="spacingMedium"></div>


    <div class="spacingMedium"></div>


  </section>

  <section id="intervention" data-nav="intervention">



    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Intervention',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Intervention</h1>
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Designing lightweight discovery inside inventory workflows</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

<div class="spacingMedium"></div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">

            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Multiple navigation and discovery models were explored to balance:</h3>


          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4 ">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ fast scanning</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ continuous context</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ discoverability </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>→ low operational overhead</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Exploration1</h5>
            <h5>Dashboard-oriented discovery</h5>

            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe_exploration1.png" alt="">

            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Strength</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> surfaced inventory opportunities</li>
              <li> exposed underlisted categories</li>
              <li> increased visibility of marketplace signals</li>

            </ul>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Tradeoff</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> introduced additional scanning overhead</li>
              <li> reduced focus on active inventory management</li>
              <li> duplicated existing dashboard behavior</li>

            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Exploration 2</h5>
            <h5>Discovery shortcuts within management</h5>

            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe_exploration2.png" alt="">

            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Strength</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> embedded promotional discovery closer to inventory workflows</li>
              <li> exposed seasonal and underused categories</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Tradeoff</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> increased interface density</li>
              <li> interrupted scanning rhythm during maintenance tasks</li>
              <li> ompeted with primary inventory actions</li>

            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Exploration 3</h5>
            <h5>Sorting & prioritization model</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe_exploration3.png" alt="">

            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Strength</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> supported visibility into high-performing or recently updated inventory</li>
              <li> enabled operational prioritization</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Tradeoff</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> introduced deeper interaction complexity</li>
              <li> increased filtering and sorting decisions during routine edits</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Revisit user behavioral insight</h3>
<h5>Provider workflows prioritized operational efficiency over feature exploration.</h5>
<h5>Providers needed:</h5>


            <ul class="listCircle">

              <li> fast scanning</li>
              <li> low-friction edits</li>
              <li> continuous context</li>
              <li> visibility into missing inventory</li>
              <li> confidence in how listings appeared on the customer-facing storefront</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Final direction</h3>

            <h5>The final system intentionally prioritized operational continuity over feature density.</h5>
            <h5>Instead of building a discovery-heavy interface, the redesign focused on:</h5>

            <ul class="listCircle">

              <li> lightweight category navigation</li>
              <li> persistent filtering</li>
              <li> inline editing</li>
              <li> unified inventory surfaces</li>
              <li> embedded storefront visibility</li>
            </ul>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>




      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <img class="modal-target card2026" src="hifi_v1_1.png" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <img class="modal-target card2026" src="hifi_v1_2.png" alt="">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight200 greyBg200 paddingXS borderRadiusXS">
              👉 Discovery remained integrated into the workflow, but secondary to fast inventory maintenance.
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Final Version</h3>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">
              After internal reviews with marketing and product stakeholders, the final version preserved the familiar category shortcut pattern to reduce behavioral disruption for existing providers.
            </h5>

            <h5>
              Advanced sorting and prioritization features were intentionally deferred to a later iteration due to implementation scope and timeline constraints.
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">


        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="hifi_final.png" alt="">


          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Key system changes</h3>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> Unified inventory into one surface, replacing multi-screen navigation</li>
              <li> Embedded category discovery directly into editing workflows</li>
              <li> Enabled inline editing to eliminate repeated context switching</li>
              <li> Persisted filters to maintain orientation during scanning and updates</li>
              <li> Surfaced listed and unlisted inventory within the same management flow</li>
              <li> Added storefront visibility tools so providers could verify customer-facing presentation during edits</li>
              <li> Improved drag-and-drop interactions with clearer visual feedback and placement behavior</li>

            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Structural shift</h3>
            <h5>From fragmented navigation to continuous inline inventory management</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4">
            <div class="Grid-cell">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint1.png" alt="Inventory spread across multiple screens">
            </div>
            <div class="Grid-cell">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint2.png" alt="4–5 clicks to edit a single item">
            </div>
            <div class="Grid-cell">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint3.png" alt="Changing categories requires restarting the flow">
            </div>
            <div class="Grid-cell">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_constraint4.png" alt="Unlisted gear not surfaced in primary workflow">
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 grey900">Before</h5>
